<!--
    ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ║  POWER PROFILE — MUST BE EXTRACTED FROM YOUR STOCK FIRMWARE        ║
    ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
    
    This file defines CPU cluster speeds, power draw per frequency,
    battery capacity, and component power consumption for your device.
    
    🔴 Using wrong values = inaccurate battery stats, CPU throttling issues
    
    TO EXTRACT YOUR DEVICE'S POWER PROFILE:
      1. Get the stock product overlay APK:
           /system/product/overlay/framework-res__auto_generated_rro_product.apk
      2. Decompile it:
           apktool d framework-res__auto_generated_rro_product.apk -o product_overlay
      3. Copy the power_profile.xml from:
           product_overlay/res/xml/power_profile.xml
      4. Replace this file with the extracted one.
    
    If there is NO power profile in the product overlay:
      - Check the vendor overlay APK at /system/vendor/overlay/
      - If neither has one, your device uses AOSP defaults — you can DELETE this file
    
    Reference: The current file was extracted from Samsung Galaxy A90 5G (SD855),
    which will NOT work correctly for other devices. DO NOT reuse it.
    
    See: https://github.com/TrebleDroid/treble_experimentations/wiki/How-to-create-an-overlay%3F
-->
<device name="Android">
    <!-- CPU and power values removed — extract from your stock firmware -->
</device>
